{
  "texts": [
    "For the subject's enfolding of the dispositif in self-conduct, see Villadsen (2021).",
    "Turing's famous \"imitation game\" itself is predicated on the indistinguishability of human and artificial intelligence (Turing 1950).",
    "In true fashion, it is not easy to confirm the attribution.",
    "What does it matter whether it was Beckett?",
    "Turns out that it was; he wrote that line-or at least he crafted it-in Texts for Nothing."
  ]
}